==English==
===Etymology===
From Afrikaans, from bil (butt), from Middle Dutch bille, + tong (tongue), from Middle Dutch tonghe. <!-- {{D.}} ''bil'': buttock + ''tong'': strip, through Afrikaans. -->
===Noun===
'''biltong'''
# (''South African English'') Food originating in South Africa.  Made by spicing meat, typically beef, with corriander, salt and pepper, then leaving it to dry out.  Similar to American beef jerky.
#*"For the uninitiated '''Biltong''' is a dried meat product made mostly in South Africa. It literally translates to "Bum Strips". Many counties have similar products but none are exactly like biltong and so representative of the taste of South Africa. Its not a pretty process or a cheap one as you lose about 50% of the weight of the uncured meat. http://www.shebeen.com/biltong/ - 19k

